On or before August 1 of each year, the local superintendent and the superintendent of the Maryland School for the Deaf shall report to the State Department of Education for the previous school year:
the number of individuals rehired under paragraph (4)(v) or (vi) or (8) of this subsection;
the school and school system where each individual was rehired; and
whether the school:
the original date of rehire for each individual;
the subject matter taught by each individual;
the annual salary of each individual; and
the percentage of student population composed of children in poverty that is required to be present in a school in that school system in order for that school to qualify as a Title 1 school.

